<subSubSection id="62DD6540197E295D7486FA1CFCA2F97C" pageId="46" pageNumber="621" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2A7836CB197E295D7486FA1CFE82FA13" blockId="46.[212,1172,1501,1691]" box="[212,320,1501,1524]" pageId="46" pageNumber="621">
<heading id="713081A7197E295D7486FA1CFE82FA13" box="[212,320,1501,1524]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="46" pageNumber="621" reason="5">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9197E295D7486FA1CFE82FA13" box="[212,320,1501,1524]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="621">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A7836CB197E295D7486F9C2FCA2F97C" blockId="46.[212,1172,1501,1691]" pageId="46" pageNumber="621">
The male differs from those of 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D48197E295D7660F9C4FD79F9FB" authorityName="Santos and Silveira" authorityYear="2009" box="[562,699,1540,1564]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="621" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9197E295D7660F9C4FD79F9FB" box="[562,699,1540,1564]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="621">M. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D48197E295D7698F9C4FC9DF9FB" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1879" box="[714,863,1541,1564]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="621" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purpurata">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9197E295D7698F9C4FC9DF9FB" box="[714,863,1541,1564]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="621">M. purpurata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D48197E295D773CF9C4FC2FF9FB" authority="Santos &amp; Melo, 2014" authorityName="Santos &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2014" box="[878,1005,1541,1564]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="621" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xavante" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9197E295D773CF9C4FC2FF9FB" box="[878,1005,1541,1564]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="621">M. xavante</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="038057A2197E295D77A7F9C5FBF1F9FC" box="[1013,1075,1540,1563]" pageId="46" pageNumber="621" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D48197E295D7020F9C4FE93F9DC" authority="Santos &amp; Melo, 2014" authorityName="Santos &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="621" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mapinguari" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9197E295D7020F9C4FE93F9DC" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="621">M. mapinguari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="038057A2197E295D7505F9E5FE51F9DC" box="[343,403,1572,1595]" pageId="46" pageNumber="621" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the shape of the medial protruding process of S4, being short and having a triangular profile in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E197E295D76EDF982FCFDF9BC" box="[703,831,1603,1627]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="17.[144,211,1402,1424]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[144,1104,168,1370]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 10. Males of Megalopta. (A, C) Frontal view of head; (B, D) frontal view of flagellomeres; (A) M. purpurata Smith (holotype) from Tefé, Brazil; (B) M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil; (C) M. yanomami sp. n. from Parauapebas, Brazil; (D) M. piraha sp. n. from Manaus, Brazil; (E) lateral view of sternum 4 of M. guarani sp. n. from Chapada dos Guimarães, Brazil; (F) posterolateral view of basal area of mesosoma M. guarani sp. n. from Chapada dos Guimarães, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm, except in E, scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004479/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="621">Figure 10E</figureCitation>
); from 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D48197E295D77CAF985FBE5F9BB" authority="Santos &amp; Melo, 2014" authorityName="Santos &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2014" box="[920,1063,1604,1628]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="621" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="karitiana" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9197E295D77CAF985FBE5F9BB" box="[920,1063,1604,1628]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="621">M. karitiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="038057A2197E295D7062F985FBADF9BC" box="[1072,1135,1604,1627]" pageId="46" pageNumber="621" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the colour of the integument, metallic green in the head and mesosoma with coppery tints (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E197E295D7544F942FE51F97C" box="[278,403,1667,1691]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="16.[212,279,1399,1421]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,168,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[212,1172,168,1367]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 9. Males of Megalopta. (A) Dorsal view of flagellum of M. guimaraesi from Formosa, Brazil; (B) ventral view of sternum 3‒4 of M. amoena from Alenquer, Brazil; (C, E) dorsal view of head; (D, F) Frontal view of head; (C) M. guarani sp. n. from Chapada dos Guimarães, Brazil; (D) M. mapinguari sp. n. from Rio Branco, Brazil; (E) M. xavante sp. n. from Nova Xavantina, Brazil; (F) M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004477" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004477/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="621">Figures 9C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E197E295D75F1F942FE12F97C" box="[419,464,1667,1691]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="17.[144,211,1402,1424]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[144,1104,168,1370]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 10. Males of Megalopta. (A, C) Frontal view of head; (B, D) frontal view of flagellomeres; (A) M. purpurata Smith (holotype) from Tefé, Brazil; (B) M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil; (C) M. yanomami sp. n. from Parauapebas, Brazil; (D) M. piraha sp. n. from Manaus, Brazil; (E) lateral view of sternum 4 of M. guarani sp. n. from Chapada dos Guimarães, Brazil; (F) posterolateral view of basal area of mesosoma M. guarani sp. n. from Chapada dos Guimarães, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm, except in E, scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004479/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="621">10F</figureCitation>
) and reddish brown on metasoma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="62DD6540197F295C74C2FF68FEABFC82" pageId="47" pageNumber="622" type="description">
<paragraph id="2A7836CB197F295C74C2FF68FECDFF27" blockId="47.[144,1104,169,647]" box="[144,271,169,192]" pageId="47" pageNumber="622">
<heading id="713081A7197F295C74C2FF68FECDFF27" box="[144,271,169,192]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="47" pageNumber="622" reason="5">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9197F295C74C2FF68FECDFF27" box="[144,271,169,192]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="622">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A7836CB197F295C74C2FF11FBCAFD60" blockId="47.[144,1104,169,647]" pageId="47" pageNumber="622">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9197F295C74C2FF11FF10FF0F" box="[144,210,208,232]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="622">Male.</emphasis>
(15) Scape with diameter gradually enlarging toward the apex. (16) Flagellum brown, except F2 reddish brown (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E197F295C7645FF31FD4EFEEF" box="[535,652,240,264]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="16.[212,279,1399,1421]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,168,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[212,1172,168,1367]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 9. Males of Megalopta. (A) Dorsal view of flagellum of M. guimaraesi from Formosa, Brazil; (B) ventral view of sternum 3‒4 of M. amoena from Alenquer, Brazil; (C, E) dorsal view of head; (D, F) Frontal view of head; (C) M. guarani sp. n. from Chapada dos Guimarães, Brazil; (D) M. mapinguari sp. n. from Rio Branco, Brazil; (E) M. xavante sp. n. from Nova Xavantina, Brazil; (F) M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004477" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004477/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="622">Figure 9C</figureCitation>
), F1–F11 not differing in diameter; F2 about two-thirds of F 
<quantity id="ED3F9B2E197F295C75C2FED1FE7DFECF" box="[400,447,272,296]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="47" pageNumber="622" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
length (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E197F295C7677FED1FD59FECF" box="[549,667,272,296]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="16.[212,279,1399,1421]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,168,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[212,1172,168,1367]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 9. Males of Megalopta. (A) Dorsal view of flagellum of M. guimaraesi from Formosa, Brazil; (B) ventral view of sternum 3‒4 of M. amoena from Alenquer, Brazil; (C, E) dorsal view of head; (D, F) Frontal view of head; (C) M. guarani sp. n. from Chapada dos Guimarães, Brazil; (D) M. mapinguari sp. n. from Rio Branco, Brazil; (E) M. xavante sp. n. from Nova Xavantina, Brazil; (F) M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004477" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004477/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="622">Figure 9C</figureCitation>
); F6–F11, in anterior view, with the anterior and posterior margins flat, in posterior view with basal glabrous area at same level of remaining surface. (17) Metanotum with integument, in dorsal view, not hidden by short plumose pillosity (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E197F295C7675FEAEFD6BFE60" box="[551,681,367,391]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="17.[144,211,1402,1424]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[144,1104,168,1370]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 10. Males of Megalopta. (A, C) Frontal view of head; (B, D) frontal view of flagellomeres; (A) M. purpurata Smith (holotype) from Tefé, Brazil; (B) M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil; (C) M. yanomami sp. n. from Parauapebas, Brazil; (D) M. piraha sp. n. from Manaus, Brazil; (E) lateral view of sternum 4 of M. guarani sp. n. from Chapada dos Guimarães, Brazil; (F) posterolateral view of basal area of mesosoma M. guarani sp. n. from Chapada dos Guimarães, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm, except in E, scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004479/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="622">Figure 10F</figureCitation>
). (18) Basal area of metapostnotum green metallic; its length 0.75× that of metanotum; smooth without longitudinal rugulosities (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E197F295C7572FE6EFE5CFE20" box="[288,414,431,455]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="17.[144,211,1402,1424]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[144,1104,168,1370]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 10. Males of Megalopta. (A, C) Frontal view of head; (B, D) frontal view of flagellomeres; (A) M. purpurata Smith (holotype) from Tefé, Brazil; (B) M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil; (C) M. yanomami sp. n. from Parauapebas, Brazil; (D) M. piraha sp. n. from Manaus, Brazil; (E) lateral view of sternum 4 of M. guarani sp. n. from Chapada dos Guimarães, Brazil; (F) posterolateral view of basal area of mesosoma M. guarani sp. n. from Chapada dos Guimarães, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm, except in E, scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004479/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="622">Figure 10F</figureCitation>
). (19) Metepisternum with sparse pilosity, integument visible through pilosity; posterior upper margin of metepisternum unmodified, lacking a velvety process (20) 1st and 2nd tarsomere of foreleg with longest simple setae shorter than the summed length of the three apical tarsomeres. (21) S3 with longitudinal sulcus, posterolateral margin notched. (22) S4 with medial protruding process, profile of process minute triangular in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E197F295C76F1FD8EFCE4FD80" box="[675,806,591,615]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="17.[144,211,1402,1424]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[144,1104,168,1370]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 10. Males of Megalopta. (A, C) Frontal view of head; (B, D) frontal view of flagellomeres; (A) M. purpurata Smith (holotype) from Tefé, Brazil; (B) M. atlantica Santos &amp; Silveira from Ipanema, Brazil; (C) M. yanomami sp. n. from Parauapebas, Brazil; (D) M. piraha sp. n. from Manaus, Brazil; (E) lateral view of sternum 4 of M. guarani sp. n. from Chapada dos Guimarães, Brazil; (F) posterolateral view of basal area of mesosoma M. guarani sp. n. from Chapada dos Guimarães, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm, except in E, scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004479/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="622">Figure 10E</figureCitation>
); basal portion glabrous; posterolateral margin notched, notched not extending to basal half of sclerite.
</paragraph>
